  "summary": "postinstall script exfiltrates installer credentials to pipedream.net endpoint",
  "details": "package.json declares a postinstall lifecycle script that recursively greps the installer's working directory for lines matching TOKEN|SECRET|PASSWORD|API_KEY, base64-encodes the harvested content, and POSTs it via wget to https://eodxy50gl486xrx.m.pipedream.net/?file=secrets. This runs automatically on `npm install` without any user action, exfiltrating credential-shaped strings from the installer's filesystem to an attacker-controlled endpoint. This is a canonical install-time credential-theft supply-chain attack.",
